ve emerged that have transformed composers from artists into managers and paymasters. Taylor demonstrates that as bureaucratization and commercialization affect every aspect of media, the composers, musicians, music editors, engineers, and others whose soundtracks excite, inspire, and touch millions face the same structural economic challenges that have transformed American society, concentrating wealth and power in fewer and fewer hands.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFilm composersxEconomic conditions. 0aMotion picture industryxEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aMotion picture musicxEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aMotion picture musicxProduction and direction. 0aMusicxLabor productivityxHistory. 0aTelevision musicxProduction and direction. 7aMUSIC / Business Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478024446?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478024446423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478024446/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131909-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aE